---> MODALS										prepared by Uğur ARSLAN, @arslanuguur
can		-ebilir, -abilir	(yetenek)		ability, doubt, astonishment, permission, polite request
could		-ebilirdi, -abilirdi	(geçmiş yetenek)
may		-ebilir, -abilir	(olasılık)		permission, if not prohibition, supposition with doubt
might		-ebilirdi, -abilirdi	(geçmiş olasılık)	
will		-acak, -ecek		(gelecek istek)		wish, desire, will, confidence, in the future
would		-acaktı, -ecekti	(ihtimal)		wish (with 'to like'), polite request, a habit of the past
shall		-acak, -ecek		(niyet)			intention, supposition
should		-malı, meli		(gereklilik)		necessity, advice, blame, recommendation, reproach, regret
must		-malı, meli		(zorundalık)		obligation, firm necessity, logical conclusion, probability
have to		-mak zorunda olmak	(zorundalık)		unwillingness, forced circumstances
had to		- mak zorunda olacaktı	(geçmiş zorundalık)
ought to	-malı, meli		(görev)			moral duty, insistent advice, strict recommendation
need to		-malı, meli		(ihtiyaç)		necessity, unnecessity
be to		-malı, meli		(zorundalık)		obligation arising out of arrangement or agreement
used to		-alışmak		(alışkanlık)		repeated action in the past
		


PRESENT			PAST			MODALS IN PAST		Concept				Example			
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
can			could			could have V3		past unreal ability		How could I have looked him in the face?
													he could have taken the flight off
													I could have lied to you
may			might			may have V3		past unreal possibility		we may have passed the math exam, but it was in French
						might have V3		past unreal small probability	you might have sold the car, if you really needed the money
													We might have done something to help you
will			would			would have V3		past unreal action		I would have said I lack the bump of paternity
shall			should			should have V3		past unreal recommendation	I should have been with them at the party tonight
													there's something I should've done a while ago
must			had to			must have V3		past unreal assumption		He must have changed clothes during the night.
have to			had to			have to have V3


be able to		was/were able to				
be supposed to		was/were supposed to



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
UNREAL STRUCTURES
	you should have done		yapmalıydın				ama yapmadı
	you ought to have done		yapmalıydın				ama yapmadı
	you may have done		yapmış olabilirsin
	you might have done		yapmış olabilirdin			ama yapmadın
	you can't have done		yapmış olamazsın
	you could have done		yapabilirdin, yapmış olabilirdin	ama yapmadın
	you couldn't have done		yapmış olamazdın
	you must have done		yapmış olmalısın
	you mustn't have done		yapmamış olmalısın
	you needn't have done		yapmana gerek yoktu 			ama boşuna yaptın
	you didn't have to do		yapmak zorunda kalmadın			
	you didn't need to do		yapmana gerek kalmadı
	you would have done		yapmış olacaktın, yapardın		ama yapmadın		
	you were to have done		yapman beklenirdi			ama yapmadın
	you were supposed to do		yapman lazımdı				ama yapmadın
	you were going to do		yapacaktın				ama yapmadın
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

--> COMPOUND MODALS
will be able to V1			she will be able to walk soon
will have to V1				he will have to wear uniform at work two days later
would be able to  V1			
would have to have V3			I would have to have broken in
should have to V1			You shouldn't have to go through this alone
had been able to V1
had had to V1
might have to V1
might be able to V1


he will have to walk on a straight line
he will have to live with the idea 
you will have to figure out the rest, first

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Obligation
	you must do - zorundasın
	you dont have to do, dont need to do, neednt do - zorunda değilsin
	you had to do - yapmak zorunda kaldın
	you didnt have to do, didnt need to do - yapmak zorunda kalmadın, yapmana gerek kalmadı
Strong Advice
	you must do - mutlaka yapmalısın
	you mustn't do - sakın yapmamalısın
	you should have done, ought to have done - yapmalıydın
	you shouldn't have done, ought not to have done - yapmamalıydın
Deduction
	you must do - yapmalısın
	you can't do - yapamazsın
	you must have done - yapmış olmalı
	you can't have done - yapmış olamaz
	you couldn't have done - yapmış olamazdı
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


---> EXAMPLES
	- He will / can / shall / must have called her
	- She would / could / should / had to have called him
	
	
	- could you help me with this math problem?				(Request)
	- you could take a painkiller, if your headache gets worse.		(Advice) 
	- Mozart could play the piano at the age of five.			(Ability)
	- she asked me if she could sit at the end of our table.		(Permission)
	- I'm going to make him an offer he can't refuse.			(Impossibility)
	- sometimes things can get crazy around here				(Possibility)
	- to be healthy, a plant has to receive a good supply of sunshine.	(Necessity)
	- would you help me to carry this heavy suitcase?			(Request)
	- may I ask whether you are using email or not?				(Permission)
	- May the Force be with you 						(Possibility)
	- if this is your first night at Fight Club, you have to fight.		(Obligation)
	- he might be fired from the work 


--> CAN
	- can you help me? 						(request)
	- I can play football, but I can not speak German. 		(ability)
	- I know he can’t drive yet, but he can dream. 			(ability)
	- we can stay home and watch telly tonight. 			(suggestion/giving an option) 
	- that can’t be her. 						o, o olamaz						(impossibility)
	- but she can come back at any time				ama o her an geri gelebilir				(possibility)
	- how can you bear that on your conscience			nasıl o vicdan yükünü taşıyorsun?
	- the lift can take four at a time				asansör bir seferde dört kişi alabilir
	- you can lead a horse to water but you can't make him drink	atı suya götürebilirsin, ama ona suyu içirtemezsin

--> COULD
	- I could do trigonometry six years ago. 			altı yıl önce trigonometri yapabilirdim			(past ability)
	- could i call you? 						seni arayabilir miyim?					(polite question)
	- she could be here. / She couldn’t be here. 			o burada olabilirdi / o burada olamazdı			(possibility / impossibility)
	- you could try doing this. 					bunu yapmayı deneyebilirdin				(suggestion)	
	- it could have gone better					daha iyi gidebilirdi					(past suggestion)

--> BE ABLE TO	
	- You were able to pass that exam with the help of the notes I gave you		(temporary ability)
		Sana verdiğim notlar sayesinde o sınavı geçebildin 
	- She isn’t able to move her arm.				Kolunu hareket ettiremiyor 				(temporary disability/negative situation)
	- I’m not able to ride a bike, my bike is broken		Bisiklete binemem, bisikletim bozuldu 
	- I can’t ride a bike, I’ve never learnt how			Bisiklete binemem, nasıl olduğunu hiç öğrenmedim

--> MAY	
	- The teacher may be late tomorrow 				Öğretmen yarın geç kalabilir				(possibility)
	- Be careful! The road may be slippery				Dikkat ol! Yol kaygan olabilir  			(possibility)
	- May i borrow your pen for a moment?				bir an için kalemini ödünç alabilir miyim? 		(Permission - Formal)

--> MIGHT
	- It might happen						o olabilirdi, o vuku bulabilirdi			(possibility)
	- She might get a scholarship this year				o bu yıl burs alabilirdi				(possibility)
	- They might be eating lunch					öğle yemeği yiyor olabilirler 				(possibility)
	- life is hard enough already. you never know what someone might be going through. just be kind
						hayat zaten yeterince zor. birinin neler yaşadığını asla bilemezsin. sadece nazik ol 
						
						
--> WILL
	- I will come back next year. 							o gelecek yıl geri gelecek	(future time)
	- if you only do what you can do, you will never be more than you are now	(future time)
	  	sadece yapabildiğini yaparsan, asla şimdiki halinden farklı olamazsın
	- I will give money to charity this new year 					bu yeni yılda bhayır kurumlarına para vereceğim 	(promise/willingness)
	- Will you have a piece/slice of cake?						bir parça/dilim kek alır mısın?				(polite question)
	- Will you let him? 								ona izin verecek misin? 				(polite question)
	- I will use the other office from now on					artık diğer ofisimi kullanacağım
	- I won’t use this office anymore						artık bu ofisi kullanmayacağım


--> WOULD
	Invitations / Preferences / Desires
	- I would like a cup of tea.						* to like - hoşlanmak, hoşuna gitmek
	- I would like to have a cup of tea
	- I would like to walk on the street					sokakta yürümek istiyorum / sokakta yürümek hoşuma gidecekti
	- would you prefer apples or oranges?					elma mı yoksa portakal mı tercih edersin?
	- which would you prefer?						hangisini tercih edersin?
	- what would be the first song you want played at your funeral?		cenazenizde çalınmasını istediğiniz ilk şarkı ne olurdu? 
	- I’m not saying ‘I hate you’ but I would unplug your life support to charge my phone
			'Senden nefret ediyorum' demiyorum ama telefonumu şarj etmek için yaşam desteğinin fişini çekerdim
 	- if the world could crumble and she wouldn't notice anything		dünya yıkılsa o hiçbir şeyin farkına varmaz
	- if I had guessed the future, I would have taken some precautions against what would happen
			geleceği tahmin etseydim olacaklara karşı önlem alırdım 


	would you mind (if) .. - sakıncası var mı?				* to mind - kafaya takmak, aldırmak, aldırış etmek, karşı çıkmak
				- would you mind closing the door? 		(polite question)
				- would you mind if I left the meeting early?	(polite question)




	prefer			--> I prefer walking to running – yürümeyi koşmaya tercih ederim
		(genel)
	would prefer ... (than)	--> I would prefer to travel by bus rather than by train
				--> I would prefer for everyone to assemble at one time, instead of meeting each individual separately.
				    herkesin aynı anda bir araya gelmesini tercih ederim, her bireyle ayrı ayrı buluşmak yerine
				--> most English people would prefer to travel in the shores of Spain rather than just offshore, rather like Caribbean.
				    İngilizlerin çoğu, Karayipler gibi açık denizde olmaktansa İspanya'nın kıyılarında seyahat etmeyi tercih ederdi. 


	would rather ... (than)	--> I would rather stay than go					gitmektense kalmayı tercih ederim
				--> he is going to sell his car, but I’d rather he didn’t
				--> I would rather go now before it gets too dark.		hava iyice kararmadan şimdi gitmeyi tercih ederim. 
	would sooner ... (than)	--> I would sooner go now before it gets too dark.		hava iyice kararmadan şimdi gitsem iyi olacak.
		(anlık)		--> he would sooner buy an opponent a drink in a pub than take their head
	would just as soon	--> I would just as soon starve than eat there again.		orada tekrar yemek yemektense açlıktan ölürüm. 
	 



--> SHALL
	- shall i help you with that? 			(offer)
	- I shall meet you there this evening. 		(confirmation)
	- you shall be the first person to know. 	(promises)

--> SHOULD
	- you should try this new dress. 		(recommend)
	- you should be more careful where you loiter.	(recommend)   - Nerelerde takıldığına daha dikkat etmelisin.
	- we should deal with this right now. 		(the right thing to do)
	- he should be home soon but i’m not sure. 	(uncertain prediction)
	- you should push harder than yesterday, if you want a different tomorrow
        - school should teach you how to become rich in your 20's, not how to retire in your 60's
	- this should not be done --> bu yapılmamalı
	- this should not have been done --> bu yapılmamalıydı

--> BE SUPPOSED TO
	- I'm supposed to be taking care of you		seninle ilgilenmem gerekiyor
	- it was supposed to be me			o ben olmalıydım
	- she wasn't supposed to be here		o burada olmamalıydı
	- how am I supposed to get my medication now?	şimdi ilaçlarımı nasıl elde etmeliyim?

--> MUST
	- She must leave. 			(probability/logical assumption)
	- She must be stuck in traffic. 	(probability/logical assumption)
	- There must be some mistake. 		(probability/logical assumption)
	- You must be back by 11 o’clock. 	(necessity)
	- You must not park your car here. 	(prohibition)
	- You must not eat my food. 		(prohibition)

--> HAS/HAVE TO	
	- People have to have an identity card 					(necessity)
	- If you want to see the sunshine, you have to weather the storm 	(necessity)
	- I have to wear a tie at work. 					(obligation)
	- She is a teacher. She has to make lesson plans 			(rules)
	- I don’t have to get up early. 					(negative)
	- She doesn’t have to clean the house 					(negative)

--> HAS/HAVE GOT TO			Alternative form of have to (“must")
	- will you tell him he has got to be more considerate? - Daha anlayışlı olmasını söyleyecek misin?
	
--> HAD TO
	- we had to work overtime yesterday. 						(past obligation)
	- we had to wake up very early this morning because our bus was at seven am.	(past necessity)


--> MANAGED TO			uğraş sonucu elde edilen başarı
	- Somehow she managed to take a few steps, and then a few more - fury driving her on.
	- he tried to talk, but he only managed to cough.




--> BE ACCUSTOMED TO		alışkın olmak
	- You will have to be more careful until you are accustomed to your strength
		Gücünüze alışana kadar daha dikkatli olman gerekecek
	- She was accustomed always to oppose anything announced in that timid tone and considered it her duty to do so	
		O ürkek ses tonuyla duyurulan her şeye her zaman karşı çıkmaya alışıktı ve bunu yapmayı bir görev sayıyordu
	- While kids might be accustomed to accessing the Internet to play games and surf the Web, 
		they may not realize that there is a world of books just waiting for them to enjoy
	Çocuklar, oyun oynamak ve Web'de gezinmek için İnternet'e erişmeye alışmış olsalar da, 
		onları eğlenmek için bekleyen bir kitap dünyası olduğunu fark etmeyebilirler
	- If you are not accustomed to getting facials, you may notice your skin becoming more blemished.
		Yüz bakımı yaptırmaya alışkın değilseniz, cildinizin daha fazla lekelendiğini fark edebilirsiniz. 
	- After I grew accustomed however, I can see just how intuitive it really is.
		Ancak alıştıktan sonra, bunun gerçekten ne kadar sezgisel olduğunu görebiliyorum. 


	
--> HAD BETTER	


--> HAVE GOT TO 


--> BE TO
	- the teacher says we are to wait here		order
	- you are not to stay up late			order
	- no one is to leave this building		order
	- the two companies are to merge shortly	arrangement
	- the prime minister is to visit Rome		arrangement
	
	BE ABOUT TO and BE ON THE POINT OF
	- the performance is about to start		near future
	- hurry up. the bus is (just) about to leave	near future
	- the bus is just going to leave		be going to
	- I am on the point of quitting my job		nearly
	
	BE DUE TO
	- the meeting is due to take place today
	- the train is due to leave at 4:20
	
	BE SET TO
	- the player is set to leave the club
	- prices are set to rise once more
	
	BE BOUND / SURE / CERTAIN TO
	- there's bound to be trouble
	- the president is sure / certain to resign
	
	WAS TO / WAS ABOUT TO
	- he fell ill on the day he was to go for a job interview
	- we saw that the bus was about to leave
	- we were on the point of buying the flat when we had second thoughts
	
	
--> Extras
	- he was getting used to getting to do
	- you've got to ask yourself one question: 'Do I feel lucky?' 
	- why should I spend money by worrying, when I'll end up just as rich?






---> COMMON VERBS
--> WANT
	- I don’t want to run into him						ona rastlamak istemiyorum
	- I don't want to get involved						ben karışmak istemiyorum
	- we dont want to cause a scene						olay çıkarmak istemeyiz
	- nobody in their right mind would want to be treated like that		hiç kimse kendisine böyle davranılmasını istemez
	- do you want to hang out again some time?				bir ara tekrar dışarda takılalım mı?

--> NEED	
	- Being smart isn’t enough, you need to fit in.				akıllı olmak yetmez, uyum içinde olmalısın			(recommend)
	- Of course I talk to myself. Sometimes I need expert advice.		tabi ki kendimle konuşurum. bazen uzman önerisine ihtiyacım var	(necessary)
	- He needed to learn for himself					yaşayarak ögrenmesi gerekiyordu
	- we don't need education, we don't need thought control		eğitime ihtiyacmız yok, düşünce kontrolüne ihtiyacmız yok
	- we don't need no education, we don't need no thought control		eğitimsizliğe ihtiyacmız yok, düşünce kontrolsüzlüğüne ihtiyacmız yok  

--> TRY
	- 
	- 
	- 


---> USED TO
	now you’re just somebody that I used to know			şimdi sen sadece eskiden tanıdığım birisin
	
	
	used to + V1 (-ardım, -erdim)
		Geçmişte sürekli olarak yapılan ama artık yapılmayan eylemleri ya da alışkanlıkları ifade ederken used to kalıbını kullanıyoruz.

	Did you use to ride a bike when you were very young?		Çok gençken bisiklet sürer miydin?
	The poor people in the village used to rely on his benevolence	Köydeki fakir insanlar onun yardımlarına güvenirdi
	My family used to live in that old house once upon a time	Ailem bir zamanlar o eski evde kalırdı. = Şimdi başka evde kalıyor
	I used to grind my teeth when I got angry during my childhood	Çocukluğumda, sinirlendiğimde dişlerimi gıcırdatırdım.= Ancak şimdi yapmıyorum
	I used to play basketball. I don’t play anymore
	Did you use to drink milk a lot? 				Eskiden çok süt içer miydin?
	Where did you use to live? 					Nerede yaşıyordun?
	She didn’t use to eat a lot, but she does now 			Eskiden çok yemezdi, ama şimdi yiyor
	She and her friend didn’t use to talk with each other		Ayşe ve arkadaşı birbirleri ile konuşmazdı
	She didn’t use to live in İstanbul 10 years ago			10 yıl önce İstanbul’da yaşamıyordu


	be used to + Ving (Alışık Olmak)
		Bu yapı “alışkanlık” ifade eder. Yani, şuanda yapıldığını gösterir. Kendisinden sonra mutlaka isim alır.
	
	I was used to waiting for hours to see my doctor		Doktorumu görmek için saatlerce beklemeye alışıktım
	I am used to getting up early					Ben erken kalkmaya alıştım
	Some students aren’t used to the snow and ice in Erzurum	Bazı öğrenciler Erzurum’daki fırtına ve kara alışkın değiller
	Women in the Anatolia are used to getting up early every day	Anadolu’daki kadınlar her gün erken kalkmaya alışkınlar
	Are you used to driving your car fast?				Arabanızı hızlı sürmeye alışık mısınız?
	I’m used to running fast.					Hızlı koşmaya alışkınım
	
	
	get used to + Ving (Gittikçe alışmak)
		Yeni yeni alışılmaya başlayan olaylarda kullanılır. Bir şeye alışmak eylemini ifade eder.
	
	He is getting used to learning how to drive a car				Araba sürmesini gittikçe öğreniyor
	They are getting used to learning how replying to my questions in English	İngilizce sorularıma cevap vermeye gittikçe alışıyorlar
	You will get used to the noise soon						Kısa süre sonra bu gürültüye alışacaksın
	I never got used to shaking hands with people all the time when I lived there	Orada yaşarken durmadan insanlarla el sıkışmaya hiç alışamadım
	I’m getting used to running away from the work nowadays owing to stress and strains in my business life
	İş hayatımdaki stres ve gerginlikler yüzünden son zamanlarda işten kaçmaya alışıyorum/adet ediniyorum



